  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "At the moment, it is not possible to set an empty graffiti value by providing `--graffiti=\"\"` as omitting the graffiti or setting it to an empty string both results in the default graffiti being used which is `Lodestar-<version>/<short-commit-sha>`. \r\n\r\nI think we should allow to explicitly set an empty graffiti as an operator might not want to use the default graffiti but also not a custom graffiti.\r\n\r\nThis is quite easy to change in terms of the implementation, it is just a matter of if we want this behavior or not.\r\n\r\nCurrent code which disallows empty graffiti\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/bc7759674f5c54013c238cb369a9d60c0635b5f9/packages/cli/src/cmds/validator/handler.ts#L184-L185\r\n\r\nFix to allow empty graffiti\r\n\r\n```ts\r\n const defaultConfig = { \r\n   graffiti: args.graffiti ?? getDefaultGraffiti(),\r\n```",
